              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SOLST"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two Counter Telescopes with Silicon",
                "Surface-Barrier Detectors of 15 and 2000 Micrometer",
                "And 7.2 and 1500 Micrometer Thickness."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SITA",
                "EDE",
                "EXTB",
                "MOMIX"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "An Excitation Curve was Measured with Two Counter",
                "Telescopes, Positioned at 15 Degrees and 25 Degrees,",
                "In Steps of 0.5-2.0 MeV in the Range E(LAB)=30-64  MeV.",
                "The Angular Distributions were Measured at E(LAB)=35,",
                "49 and 62 MeV, Whereby the Two Telescopes were Used",
                "From 10 to 90 Degrees and 90 to 170 Degrees,",
                "Respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "INTAD",
                "INTED"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "To Obtain the Excitation Curve the Differential",
                "Cross Sections, Measured As a Function of Bombarding",
                "Energy at Two Angles Only, were Converted Into Total",
                "Cross Sections by Normalization Factors Interpolated",
                "Between Those at the Three Energies at Which Angular",
                "Distributions were Measured. This Procedure was",
                "Justified by the Fact That these Factors Change Less",
                "Than 10% Between 35 and 62 MeV.",
                "A Small Hydrogen Contamination in the Target Yielded",
                "A Sharp Proton-Knockout Peak Which was Subtracted",
                "Before Integrating."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The Absolute Cross Sections have an",
                "Estimated Uncertainty of 7%.  For the Values of the",
                "Excitation Curve a Standard Deviation of 3% was Found",
                "By Comparing Two or Three Independent Measurements Made",
                "At 17 Energies."
              ]
            }
          ],
